## 12. Common Mistakes & Key Takeaways

| Mistake | Fix |
|---------|-----|
| Listing features not benefits | Transform specs into user benefits |
| Same opening every time | Vary opening hooks |
| Ignoring target audience | Adapt language for the buyer persona |
| Keyword stuffing | Use keywords naturally |

| # | Takeaway |
|---|----------|
| 1 | **Audience-targeted descriptions** outperform generic ones |
| 2 | **Benefits > features** — customers care about what the product does for them |
| 3 | **SEO-natural writing** ranks better than keyword-stuffed copy |
| 4 | **Template + LLM hybrid** gives consistency with variety |
| 5 | **Quality rubrics** make copy evaluation systematic |

